<paragraph blockId="34.[144,403,1394,1418]" box="[144,403,1394,1418]" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">
<emphasis box="[144,403,1394,1418]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[144,944,1434,1458]" box="[144,944,1434,1458]" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">
Known only from the vicinity of the Abrolhos Reefs, 
<collectingCountry box="[750,818,1434,1458]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[831,927,1434,1458]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[58,125,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[186,1466,455,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-51@4.[186,1466,455,1336]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Map of distribution of reef octocorals in different regions off the Brazilian coastline. The Espírito Santo State area (*) includes the Vitória- Trindade seamount chain. “BA Sector” refer to a division of reef areas in Bahia State by Leão (1996)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207418/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Figure 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[144,243,1506,1530]" box="[144,243,1506,1530]" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">
<emphasis box="[144,243,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[144,1104,1546,1698]" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">
The last decade has seen a surge of research on Brazilian reefs (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Castro CB &amp; Pires DO" pageId="34" pageNumber="796" pagination="357 - 371" refId="ref26103" refString="Castro CB, Pires DO. 2001. Brazilian coral reefs: what we already know and what is still missing. Bull Mar Sci. 69 (2): 357 - 371." type="journal article" year="2001">Castro and Pires 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Castro" authorityYear="1989" box="[339,429,1578,1602]" class="Anthozoa" family="Plexauridae" genus="Plexaurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="34" pageNumber="796" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="regia">
<emphasis box="[339,429,1578,1602]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">P. regia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still only recorded from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[849,918,1578,1602]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, especially from the Abrolhos Bank. It is a shallow-water, large and conspicuous species, easy to identify in the field. It seems to be restricted to offshore (&gt; 
<quantity box="[770,828,1642,1666]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="796" unit="km" value="5.0">5 km</quantity>
from the coast) reefs of southern 
<collectingRegion box="[250,319,1674,1698]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="34" pageNumber="796">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, approximately from Porto Seguro to the Abrolhos Bank.
</paragraph>
